cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper deals with advanced interference management techniques for multi-beam satellite systems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), communication and security (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper discusses the design of a geographical scheduling algorithm for multicast precoding, which involves the optimization of resource allocation and transmission scheduling, and can be applied to various CS sub-fields. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.COMM, cs.SY, and cs.DC.
